The paper deals with the problem of image co-localization, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel approach to learning a common object detector, which involves an entropy-based objective function. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper uses a segmentation approach to refine the localization, which could make it relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as well.
